* Creating a system disk for the Optical Disk Copy Utility* By Kip Olson, September, 1988** This DO file can be used to create a system disk for use in the* optical disk copy box. The diskette must be copy-protected or the* copy utility will not run.** Make a copy-protected diskold protect.; run** Create a system diskold :monitor; sav f0:old :.system:.ld-7; sav f0:new .workset type datasav f0:,100** Create a subcatalog for the index filescre f0:.index,l 1200cre f0:.index1,l 1200** Create a log file for the copy utilitynew copylogsav f0:,100** Use VOLUME to find out the volume name and serial no. of the source volumeold volume.; sav f0:volume** Use UPDATE to create an index file for the source volumeold update.; sav f0:update** Use OPCOPY to copy optical disksold opcopy.; sav f0:opcopy